gives them a computer.

00:22:00.550 --> 00:22:05.190 align:middle line:84%
I've seen people get cars,
get jobs, get raises.

00:22:05.190 --> 00:22:07.300 align:middle line:84%
I'm not a big lottery
person because I

00:22:07.300 --> 00:22:10.590 align:middle line:84%
think that's a weirdness
and might be personal thing.

00:22:10.590 --> 00:22:12.340 align:middle line:84%
I'm not going to
say go win lottery.

00:22:12.340 --> 00:22:14.020 align:middle line:84%
I don't give you
lottery numbers.

00:22:14.020 --> 00:22:18.700 align:middle line:84%
But it's asking the universe,
you changing your perception.

00:22:18.700 --> 00:22:22.360 align:middle line:84%
Literally, you're sacrificing
your dollar bill, the old sac--

00:22:22.360 --> 00:22:23.665 align:middle line:90%
and it just works.

00:22:23.665 --> 00:22:26.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Why does
this work for me?

00:22:26.260 --> 00:22:30.370 align:middle line:84%
I will-- whether it's Los
Angeles, or Boulder, Colorado,

00:22:30.370 --> 00:22:33.400 align:middle line:84%
or St. Louis, see
a homeless person.

00:22:33.400 --> 00:22:36.850 align:middle line:84%
And it's very difficult
for me to go past them

00:22:36.850 --> 00:22:38.920 align:middle line:90%
without giving them something--

00:22:38.920 --> 00:22:40.840 align:middle line:90%
$5, $20.

00:22:40.840 --> 00:22:43.450 align:middle line:84%
I've even given $100
every once in a while,

00:22:43.450 --> 00:22:45.010 align:middle line:90%
just to see their face.

00:22:45.010 --> 00:22:48.390 align:middle line:84%
Actually, that's one
of the reasons I do it.

00:22:48.390 --> 00:22:51.670 align:middle line:84%
And it's to help them, but
it makes you feel good.

00:22:51.670 --> 00:22:55.960 align:middle line:84%
But why is it when you
do that, it seems that it

00:22:55.960 --> 00:22:57.263 align:middle line:90%
comes back to you five times?

00:22:57.263 --> 00:22:58.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NEGRI: Because
that's the exact rule--

00:22:58.930 --> 00:23:00.430 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: I mean,
here's an example--

00:23:00.430 --> 00:23:04.270 align:middle line:84%
I gave a homeless person who
was outside the post office

00:23:04.270 --> 00:23:08.675 align:middle line:84%
in Sherman Oaks,
California, $20.

00:23:08.675 --> 00:23:10.300 align:middle line:84%
He was sitting there
with a little sign

00:23:10.300 --> 00:23:11.410 align:middle line:90%
right outside the door.

00:23:11.410 --> 00:23:14.140 align:middle line:84%
